## Require (verb-specific)

- **(R-Q1)** External quantum-resource SSOT = `~/core/qmirror` standalone (v2.0.0+, 8/8 cond). hexa-bio is **consumer-only**: never modify qmirror canonical files from this session (memory `feedback_cross_repo_canonical`). The SSOT change of consumers `+="hexa-bio"` lives in qmirror/nexus repo session.
- **(R-Q2)** raw#9 spirit: stdlib-only Python in `_python_bridge/module/`. `numpy`/`scipy` allowed only when essential (Aer python bridge invocation already concedes `qiskit`). Current pipeline uses no numpy/scipy in hexa-bio code; Aer is invoked via subprocess + JSON.
- **(R-Q3)** Hamiltonian coefficients: hardcoded per molecule per cycle (Kandala 2017 H₂ baseline). PySCF re-derivation is a separate cycle deliverable; coefficient drift is tracked per-cell in registry rows.
- **(R-Q4)** Bridge I/O: hexa-bio adapter passes `QMIRROR_ROOT` env explicitly. Other env (HEXA_FORK_CAP, cwd) historically required (cycle-26 cleanup verify, 2026-05-06) but redundant after qmirror's own path/fork robustness fix. Inline history caveat in `quantum_entropy_qmirror.py:145–152`.
- **(R-Q5)** Falsifier evidence: every closed cell ships a selftest sentinel `__HEXA_BIO_Q*__ ALL PASS` line + a one-shot wall-clock measurement appended to the canonical doc (§17 production-smoke pattern).

